slaves of suspected Patriots.

159
00:09:35,553 --> 00:09:37,990
I am sincerely sorry

160
00:09:38,024 --> 00:09:40,060
that you're being punished
for your husband's actions,

161
00:09:40,095 --> 00:09:44,064
but he is a confirmed insurrectionist,
madam, not a suspected one.

162
00:09:45,768 --> 00:09:48,835
These poor souls have never
had to provide for themselves.

163
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:51,672
And now you give them a mere seven days

164
00:09:51,706 --> 00:09:53,475
to prepare for a life
they have never known.

165
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:56,412
Were their forefathers
given a chance to prepare

166
00:09:56,446 --> 00:09:58,647
when they were plucked
from the Dark Continent

167
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:00,651
and introduced to these shores?

168
00:10:02,121 --> 00:10:06,025
Sir, I have known some
of them all my life and...

169
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,893
Slavery is a sin,

170
00:10:07,927 --> 00:10:10,926
<i>which is why it has just been
legally abolished in England</i>

171
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:13,595
and, I expect, soon
throughout the Crown Colonies.

172
00:10:13,630 --> 00:10:17,400
<i>The Dunmore Proclamation will be upheld.</i>

173
00:10:19,001 --> 00:10:21,602
The able men will go to New
York and join the war effort,

174
00:10:21,636 --> 00:10:24,105
<i>and as for the women, I've already arranged</i>

175
00:10:24,139 --> 00:10:26,538
